Who am I? Maybe an intellectual bohémienne! Full of adventure, born in Amsterdam, there after moved 21 times ,Paris, New York, Danmark etc. but  Amsterdam will always be my favourite!. I am interpreter at court in French and Danish, and free lance violin player in several orchestra's, chamber music is my favourite.  I have 2 adorabal kids and 7 grand childs!  With our dog, a very enjoyable sweet little bastard, we are THE  happy family ! In 1992 I build the very first floating hotel in Amsterdam "La Casalo"which was known world wide because  is was so personal and so different. Only 4 rooms which made it possible to have a deeper contact with the guests. That such a small hotel would attract celebrities looking for privacy  was a happy suprise to me. I had a lot of fun with those  very special guests, artists, business men, we all had a wonderful time. In 1998 I sold La Casalo, it was a hard decision, but I needed my freedom back! And ..I got it and enjoy every minute of life, making music , fooling around with my small grand childs , sailing and our holidays in Bretagne,You may know that my "luxe" is nature and love , for me Luxe has nothing to do with money or glamour. I prefer staying in a little chalet or a mobilhome than in a big hotel with Jaccuzzi! Nature around my boat is something special in the middle of city life. Once I was a farmer - in Denmark - and i know that we will move to the country as soon as we found the wright place. i can not wait.

I have always been fascinated by storytelling and political campaigning and managed to make a living out of this fascination. I have been working in the field of politics and campaigning for many years now and I was involved in legalizing airbnb in Amsterdam recently, a great project to work on for the city.

Furthermore I love cinema, basketball, cooking, dining, wine, springtime and long walks. With the ones I love, of course. 

I started booking with airbnb 3 years ago and knowing the joy of staying in a great and homy place only recently (May 2014) decided to be part of the sharing economy all the way and share my place and knowledge of this city with like minded travelers around the world. about:
We are Jaap (53) and Marijke (45) with our children Hannah (13) and Ytse (11). We rent 2 different apartments:

On the Amstel River, we rent a downstairs apartment (completely renovated in 2014) with a double bed, a sleeping couch plus extra matress plus all the furniture, kitchen and a very large, private bathroom. This floor - 80m2 - is suited for longer stays. Fully furnished with washer/dryer, internet, TV, spacious study room etc.  Our house - from 1900 - is right on the Amstel river with a garden at the back. You can easily walk downtown (10 minutes) along the tree-lined riverfront with houseboats. You can park in front or we have detailed 'cheaper parking' instructions. We are at 200m from Metrostation Wibautstraat and 600m. from Amstel Station (train, subway, tram, bus). 

Also we rent a one-bedroom apartment in the East-side of the Centre, near the Nautical Museum. Complete kitchen, washing machine etc., very quite area.

We hope to hear from you!

Wij kijken er naar uit om u te verwelkomen in Amsterdam!

about:
We're Anna and Maarten and we would like to invite into our beautiful home on the Amstel River. A place that we've enjoyed for many years now and many more to come. Because we have two small boys (Philip and Alexander) and can still travel before they have to go to school we've decided to share our house with you when we're abroad. 

We fell in love with this house the second we walked into the door. Right in the center of town but with the peace and quiet of the Amstel River in front of us. With the vibrant Pijp to the left and the wonderful Utrechtsestraat to the right you can just walk out of our door to discover the beauty of this awesome city immediately.

about: Dave  (47 years) is  from Amsterdam, The Netherlands working with KLM Royal Dutch Airlines with the pilot department (office job). Ruud is 45 years, owner of a small catering office in Amsterdam. Both of us love New York and try to visit it as much as possible.

Hi, we're Jasper and Eva. Together we run an interior design company where Jasper, as a designer, is the creative mind and founder of the company. Eva is responsible for a lot of communication and organization behind the scenes.

When we are in Amsterdam we love to go to museums and theaters, festivals and nice restaurants or tour over the canals since we both can sail. We made a little manual for our guests that includes some nice spots in the neighbourhood, but always feel free to ask for some more up-to-date tips!

Besides Amsterdam, we love to travel to sunny places or go for a ski in the winter. Last December we traveled for the first time with AirBnb when we celebrated our anniversary in New York. We loved the experience and enjoy meeting people that love to travel as much as we do. Hopefully our houseboat can be the perfect home for you to experience Amsterdam in a unique way!

The newly build houseboat was kind of Jaspers prestige project. It took him, and a team of professional boat builders, 2 years to complete it from its steel scratch casco. Now that it's finished we are more than happy with the result and love to share it with the AirBnb community!

We hope to see you soon, you're welcome!
